VERDICT: REVISE

- **P2 — The live landing and playground violate their stated ≤6px/no-shadow styling contract.** `app/page.tsx:243-247` and `components/playground/PlaygroundClient.tsx:83-87` render `.lp-btn`, but `app/globals.css:952-980` gives it an 8px radius and decorative normal/hover shadows. Override those properties to ≤6px/no shadow, or record an explicit exception and correct the contract.

- **P2 — The site-slice “ONE prose change” claim is inaccurate.** The adjudicated lede change is at `app/page.tsx:237-240`, but the commit also introduces visible catch copy at `app/page.tsx:253-268`: a new eyebrow, heading, and multi-sentence explanation. Append a correction clarifying that the lede was the only change to pre-existing prose, while the catch section added new prose.

- **P2 — The browser import-graph proof is fail-open.** `evals/packs/playground-golden.test.ts:72-100` uses a regex that misses `import("node:fs")`, `require("node:fs")`, and TypeScript import-equals; it ignores most bare packages and unresolved local imports. Direct probes produced zero matches for all three hidden forms. Replace it with a TypeScript-AST or bundler-metafile closure walk, check the complete Node builtin list, and fail on unresolved/unapproved imports. The current closure appears browser-safe; the claimed proof is not sound.

- **P2 — Structurally malformed feeds can escape the promised “No verdict” error path.** `components/playground/verify-in-browser.ts:62-73` accepts any object containing an array and casts it to `AcpFeed`; `lib/packs/listings/adapters.ts:44-52` then dereferences every member. Input such as `{"items":[null]}` throws, while `components/playground/PlaygroundClient.tsx:49-60` has no defensive catch. Runtime-validate complete item shapes, catch engine failures, and test null rows, missing fields, and wrong field types.

- **P2 — The edited-feed e2e does not prove replay is impossible.** `evals/e2e/playground.spec.ts:29-48` tests one known edit and only requires a non-golden tally plus a generic missing-row message. A two-case canned implementation could pass. The implementation is genuinely live by source inspection, but the test claim is overstated. Mutate unpredictable values and assert their exact engine-derived receipts, preferably across multiple distinct edits; until then, label this as input-sensitivity evidence.

- **P2 — Mandatory continuity records are stale at committed HEAD.** `4253057:CURRENT_TASK.md:6`, `HANDOFF.md:9`, `PROJECT_STATE.md:3`, and `docs/task-log.md:1578-1580` still say B-2 adoption and playground commissioning are awaiting owner action; `docs/implementation-journal.md` has no entry for either meaningful slice. This violates the repository continuity contract and can send the next session backward. Sync the state/task/handoff/log/journal records before push.

